  "prompt": "How can I link Instagram to some group in my Facebook?",
  "response": "To link Instagram to a Facebook group, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Facebook and go to the group you want to link\n\n2. Click on \"More\" (three dots) or \"Edit Group\"\n\n3. Look for \"Linked Accounts\" or \"Instagram Integration\" option\n\n4. Select \"Link Instagram Account\"\n\n5. You'll be prompted to log into Instagram\n\n6. Choose the Instagram account you want to link\n\n7. Confirm the connection\n\nNote: Both accounts must have the same admin or be owned by the same person. Also, not all group types support direct Instagram linking.\n\nIf you're having trouble, you can also:\n- Manually share Instagram posts to the group\n- Use Facebook's cross-posting features\n- Add Instagram content through Facebook's sharing tools\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
